    "content": "**Yes.** This works. The main text carries the natural term, the TN supplies the structural precision. No issues from the Chinese philosophy side.\n\nOne small suggestion for the TN wording: rather than just \"pre-nihilist metaphysics,\" make it slightly fuller so the reader gets the full tripartite structure in one glance:\n\n> [TN: The author's term 前形而上学 (qian xing er shang xue), literally \"pre-metaphysics,\" refers to metaphysics as practiced before the nihilistic crisis -- i.e., the entire metaphysical tradition from its origins through to the collapse of its highest values. The author's periodization is: traditional metaphysics (前形而上学) -> nihilism (虚无主义) -> post-metaphysics (后形而上学).]\n\nThis way the reader sees the full arc on first encounter and does not need to reconstruct it later.\n"
